      "content": "Do NOT perform the Valsalva maneuver, as forcefully blowing your nose could cause a ruptured eardrum or push infected/debris wax deeper, worsening the blockage. Sudden, sensorineural hearing loss (inner ear damage) can become permanent within hours if not treated promptly with steroids, but conductive loss (wax or drum damage) often resolves on its own. Since you have no pain, your symptoms strongly suggest inner ear damage or significant wax impaction rather than a rupture; you have roughly 24 hours before it might be permanent, but getting an ENT specialist to diagnose immediately via an otoscope is far safer and far quicker than waiting. Please find a nearby clinic like Amelie Ost or a hospital ER immediately, as waiting until morning is unnecessary given the risk of permanent nerve damage.",
